President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 26 through June 1, 2013, as National Hurricane Preparedness Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of being prepared for hurricane season and highlights the devastating impact that hurricanes can have on coastal communities. The President acknowledges the heroic efforts of first responders and the resilience of ordinary citizens in the face of disaster. He urges families to take simple steps such as building a supply kit, learning evacuation routes, and developing a disaster plan. The Federal Government is committed to supporting emergency management partners and improving hurricane forecasting. The proclamation calls upon government agencies, private organizations, schools, media, and residents in coastal areas to share information about hurricane preparedness and response.